          "evidence_text_excerpt": "ross\u00a0all of your CIBC eAdvantage Savings Accounts\u00a0with the same accountholders. You can earn Smart Interest on balances up to $200,000. Full limitations are set out in the Terms and Conditions.\nTip: Try to avoid scheduling automatic transfers on the last day of the month. These transfers will fall on the \"next business day\" so they will not count towards your Smart Interest balance growth for the current month.\nYes. You can earn Smart Interest on your account balances up to\u00a0$200,000. This is called the \"Smart Balance Maximum.\" If you have multiple CIBC eAdvantage Savings Accounts, the Smart Balance Maximum will apply across all your accounts with the same accountholders.\nSmart Interest is calculated daily at the current Smart Interest rate on your full closing balance each day up to a maximum balance of $200,000.\u00a0Smart Interest will be paid between the first 5 to 7 business days of the",
